# Trivy ignore file for Code Engine image scan.
# These CVEs are in transitive dependencies we cannot directly control.

# jackson-core inside ray_dist.jar (bundled in ray pip package).
# Cannot upgrade without a new ray release. Low risk: JAR is not
# directly exposed — ray is a transitive dep of qiskit-serverless.
GHSA-72hv-8253-57qq

# mathjax <3.2.1 — prototype pollution via crafted MathML input.
# Bundled inside jupyter_server/nbconvert; cannot upgrade independently.
CVE-2023-39663

# underscore.js <1.12.1 — arbitrary code execution via template function.
# Bundled inside jupyter_server/nbclassic; cannot upgrade independently.
CVE-2026-27601

# gpgv (Debian OS package) — signature verification bypass.
# Transitive OS-level dep from base image; no direct control.
CVE-2025-68973

# pyarrow 21.0.0 — use-after-free (DoS) when reading a crafted Arrow IPC
# *file* with pre-buffering + variadic buffers. Fixed in 23.0.1, but
# qiskit-serverless 0.32.0 (latest) hard-pins pyarrow<22, so the fix is
# not installable until upstream relaxes that ceiling. Low real risk: the
# image is a Jupyter tutorial sandbox; nothing parses untrusted Arrow IPC
# files. Re-evaluate when qiskit-serverless allows pyarrow>=23.
CVE-2026-25087

# jackson-databind 2.18.6 — unsafe-polymorphic deserialization gadgets
# (both HIGH; PolymorphicTypeValidator bypass and array-subtype allowlist
# bypass). Fixed in 2.18.8/2.21.4/3.1.4. The flagged jar is vendored
# *inside* ray_dist.jar (ray/jars/ray_dist.jar); ray is a transitive dep of
# qiskit-serverless. jackson is not pip-installable — the fix only arrives
# when Ray rebundles a patched jackson. Exploitable only when attacker-
# controlled JSON is deserialized with default typing enabled; nothing we
# ship drives Ray's JVM deserialization on untrusted input. Same posture as
# upstream QuBins/qiskit-images. Drop once Ray rebundles jackson>=2.18.8.
CVE-2026-54512
CVE-2026-54513
